In this proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on April 30, 2018, he declares May 2018 as Jewish American Heritage Month. The proclamation recognizes the profound contributions that the Jewish faith and its traditions have had on the United States. It highlights the historic speech delivered by Mordecai Noah in 1818, where he proclaimed that Jews in America could now feel equal and protected. The proclamation also acknowledges the strong commitment of Jewish Americans to engage in American society while preserving their values and traditions. It emphasizes the Jewish community's contributions to American society, including their involvement in civil rights movements, their service in the military, and their achievements in literature, music, cinema, and the arts. The proclamation concludes by calling upon all Americans to celebrate the heritage and contributions of American Jews during the month of May.